<section id="exam-builder" style="font-family:Segoe UI,Arial,sans-serif; margin:20px 0;">
  <h2 style="color:#1a3d7c;">Exam Builder</h2>

  <p>
    The Exam Builder is responsible for converting a structured Google Spreadsheet into a
    complete APL‑ES exam package. It validates the input, extracts the three required forms,
    applies column‑level transformations, and produces a standardized ZIP bundle ready for
    import into the APL‑ES runtime.
  </p>

  <h3 style="margin-top:25px;">Architecture Overview</h3>
  <p>The Exam Builder follows a simple, transparent processing pipeline:</p>

  <ol>
    <li><strong>Fetch Spreadsheet</strong> – The tool retrieves three named sheets from a Google Spreadsheet using fixed ranges.</li>
    <li><strong>Normalize Data</strong> – Columns are cleaned, blanked (where required), and validated.</li>
    <li><strong>Transform to CSV</strong> – Each sheet is converted into a CSV representation.</li>
    <li><strong>Package</strong> – All CSV files are bundled into a ZIP archive.</li>
    <li><strong>Load / Reload</strong> – The ZIP can be imported directly into APL‑ES to refresh the exam content.</li>
  </ol>

  <div style="margin:20px 0; padding:15px; background:#eef3ff; border-left:4px solid #1a73e8;">
    <strong>Note:</strong> The Exam Builder supports both FULL and STUDENT versions of the exam,
    with optional inclusion of Learning Notes.
  </div>

  <h3 style="margin-top:25px;">Spreadsheet Layout Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    The Google Spreadsheet must contain <strong>three forms</strong>, each with a specific structure.
    These forms define the questions, section/part hierarchy, and exam metadata.
  </p>

  <h4 style="margin-top:20px;">1. <code>examQuestions</code></h4>
 

  <h4 style="margin-top:20px;">2. <code>sectionPartTitles</code></h4>
  

  <h4 style="margin-top:20px;">3. <code>examData</code></h4>
 
  <h3 style="margin-top:25px;">Future Enhancements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Support for direct CSV uploads (no Google Sheets required)</li>
    <li>Visual validation of spreadsheet structure</li>
    <li>Interactive architecture diagram</li>
    <li>Auto‑generated documentation from spreadsheet headers</li>
  </ul>

</section>
<h3 style="margin-top:25px;">CSV Output</h3>
  <p>
    After processing, the Exam Builder produces three CSV files with the same structure as the
    input sheets. These are packaged into a ZIP archive for import into APL‑ES.
  </p>

  <p>
    Certain columns (such as internal notes or instructor‑only fields) may be automatically
    blanked depending on the selected build mode (FULL, STUDENT, or STUDENT+Learning).
  </p>
